This paper is about face alignment using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a multistage model that utilizes spatial transformer networks, hourglass networks, and exemplar-based shape constraints, which are all techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for face alignment, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
